icpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 Once everyone has taken their turn, the last player will need to tap the End of Round button.\u8220 ;}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 DONE}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 1801}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 Yee-haw! Congratulations on making it through your first year in town! With all the new people moving in to town, we\u8217 re starting to expand! Harvesters are starting to stockpile resources, and farmers\u8217  fields are starting to grow.}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 Now after you\u8217 ve gathered your wood/clay or harvested your crops, you\u8217 ll need a way to sell them.}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 Everyone can sell their goods directly to the town if they want to, and buy them from the town as well: you can see the current price the town will pay, and how much money the town has here.}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 You may never buy more goods than are available and may never sell more goods than the town has money to buy.}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 But you get to decide if you want to start out by focusing on selling things here in town, or selling them in a neighboring town where our natural resources might have more value.}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 So, you can have either a mule, which will let you take some of your supplies to neighboring towns where the market might be better, or a store, which will let you sell some of your goods for an extra cent here in town.}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 Go around and let players choose. Hand them their cards and place them.}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 Great, so we\u8217 ll go around and take our turns again. Again, you can take one \u8220 Land Action\u8221  and as many \u8220 Town Actions\u8221  as you\u8217 d like. Farmers, on this turn that means you can harvest your crops, and anyone who has a mule can decide to travel if they want to.}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 you have two pieces of land and you have a couple options for how you can use it:}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 you can use the natural resources on it for free (take a card fill it up...)}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 or you can build a farm, store or mule. They require the resources in the top right corner.}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 a mule allows you to travel to a neighboring town with two goods which you can sell in their markets. Different towns have different needs and may have very different market prices.}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 Players take their turns.}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 DONE}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 1803}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 A land office has been built! This is a new Town Action you can take during your turn. If someone starts a land auction, the town will start to bid off a piece of land.}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 The starting bid is 5 cents going to the player that called for the action. Anyone in town may bid on the land and the bidding continues until the highest bidder is uncontested.}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 The winner then pays the town, claims the land, and may build a natural resource on it for free, or pay extra resources to build another type of building.}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 And money isn\u8216 t the only thing that has value: At the end of the game you also get money for the value of your land, which is on the bottom right hand side of whatever building you place. The town will only auction land twice per year.}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 DONE}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 1806}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 Word of the prosperity in your town is spreading and it\u8216 s attracting workers! Workers are very valuable because they allow you to take an extra Land Action each turn.}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 Hiring workers is a Town Action, and you can hire as many workers as are available. But each one gets more expensive and once a player hires one no one else in that town can.}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 At the beginning of every year a worker will show up to the two towns with the highest Player Wealth in the region, that is, the towns that have the highest total money amongst their citizens.}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 DONE}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 1808}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 As the years pass, technology is starting to get better and better! You\u8217 ve now got access to covered wagons! Wagons allow you to carry more goods when travelling!}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;}\uc0 DONE}{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\f